attributes.description:
Travelers should consider:
-Yellow Fever vaccination;
-Hepatitis A and Hepatitis B vaccines;
-Typhoid vaccine for visits to smaller cities or rural areas;
-Routine vaccines including Measles;
-Yellow Fever vaccination for travelers aged 9 months or older who are visiting areas of Colombia that are not the following: all areas above 2300 meters, the department of San Andres y Providencia, the capital city of Bogota, and the cities of Barranquilla, Cali, Cartagena, and Medellin.

Additional vaccine recommendations may apply. Consult your healthcare provider and check the source for details.
